  1. Top 10 teams based on no of total matches won

  1. Top 10 teams based on toss winning and match winning
temp_table = merge(x = match, y = team,by.x = "Team_Name_Id",by.y = "Team_Id",all.x = 1)
View(temp_table)

 
temp1 = merge(x=temp_table[ ,c(1,2,7,14,21)],y = team[ ,1:2],by.x ="Toss_Winner_Id",by.y = "Team_Id",all.x = 1 )
View(temp1)

winner = temp1 %>% group_by(Team_Name)%>% filter(Toss_Winner_Id == Match_Winner_Id)%>%
  summarise(number_win = sum(n()))%>% arrange(-number_win)%>% head(10)
View(winner)

#question7
plot7 <- ggplot(winner, aes(x=reorder(Team_Name, -number_win), y=number_win)) + geom_bar(stat = 'identity', width = 0.5, fill = "gold2") + theme_bw() + labs(x='Team Name',y='No of Toss & Won',title="Top 10 teams based on toss winning and match winning") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))
print(plot7)

              by.x = "Man_Of_The_Match_Id",by.y = "Player_Id",all.x = TRUE)

               by.x ="Team_Id",by.y = "Team_Id",all.x =TRUE)

#question8
